## Flow

- The customer sends daily data to https://inventtecovasshared.blob.core.windows.net/invent-tecovas-input/in Microsoft Azure Storage every night. The daily folder is of the format yyyy-mm-ddThhmmss.sssz i.e. `2025-04-28T080015.172Z´
- The task in the our daily runner DAG moves the file from the invent-tecovas-inputfolder to the historyfolder.
- Tecovas to drop data on Azure blob by 3am Central, daily. Inventory files are to be provided earlier than 3am, when possible. Current runtime is max 5hrs, and we promise the UI is available to business users by 8am CT (Austin, TX).
- The Airflow job starts at around 09:00 AM UTC every day and is expected to finish by 12.00 UTC

- Ad-hoc allocations are also once-off orders, but are different from Manual Orders in that the order quantities for product/store combinations are calculated by Invent, whereas Manual Orders require that the quantity be input from the user

## Proof of Value Rollout

A 6 week Proof of Value phase will precede full rollout. During this time, [invent.ai](http://invent.ai) will manage the replenishment and allocations for a group of stores. Tecovas will continue managing a comparable group of stores. At the end of 6 weeks, the Weighted In-Stock % for the last 4 weeks will be compared to prove the value created by the [invent.ai](http://invent.ai) solution, prior to full rollout.

A criss-cross strategy will be followed to reduce bias between the comparable Tecovas vs Invent managed sets:

- Test Stores: Invent manages Footwear, Tecovas manages Apparel & Accessories
- Control Stores: Invent manages Apparel & Accessories, Tecovas manages Footwear

Tecovas will plan their allocations on a single day of the week (Tuesday), but will upload these orders to the warehouse daily according to the Order Schedule. ### Reporting: New Item/Store Eligibility Planning

Tecovas would like a report that can aid decision making for assortment planning: to ensure they have sufficient inventory to stock planned stores with New Items. Today, Tecovas does a pre-allocation 6-8wks prior to launch and will then adjust the scope (store eligibility) for that New Item if they notice that in fact they would not have enough inventory to stock all eligible stores. In that case they would then remove the eligibility of that New Item from lower performing stores. This is trully an Assortment Planning scope, so cannot be accommodate as a system generated recommendation, but instead [invent.ai](http://invent.ai) can aid the business by providing a report that shows the spread/depth of each New Item based on the planned scope. Not required for go live, but desired. Further workshop required.
